gallows
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:A wooden frame, usu. of two uprights and a crosspiece, on which carcases are hung to be dressed. See also Spanish gallows.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: (farmers') also as meat gallows
